  To apply for a Fee Grant and Course Grant download and fill in form PTGN.

  **Academic year** | **Form**
  2016 to 2017 | [PTGN - form (PDF, 615KB)](http://media.slc.co.uk/sfe/1617/pt/sfe_ptgn_form_1617_d.pdf)
  2016 to 2017 | [PTGN - guidance notes (PDF, 100KB)](http://media.slc.co.uk/sfe/1617/pt/sfe_ptgn_notes_1617_d.pdf)

  You can apply up to 9 months after your course starts.

  ## You or your partner get benefits

  You need to download and fill in [form CB1 (PDF, 463KB)](http://media.slc.co.uk/sfe/1617/pt/sfe_pt_cb1_form_1617_d.pdf) if you or your partner gets:

  - Universal Credit
  - Income Support
  - Income-based Jobseeker’s Allowance (JSA)
  - Income-related Employment Support Allowance (ESA)
  - Housing Benefit
  - Local Housing Allowance

  ## Your circumstances have changed

  You need to download and fill in [form CO2 (PDF, 98KB)](http://media.slc.co.uk/sfe/1617/pt/sfe_pt_co2_form_1617_d.pdf) if you’ve changed:

  - your course, or left it
  - university or college
  - your name, address or contact details

